results.name: Square array A(n,k), n>=0, k>=1, read by antidiagonals, where row n is the sum of n-th powers of unitary divisors of k (divisors d such that gcd(d, k/d) = 1).
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Unitary Divisor
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Unitary Divisor Function
Index entries for sequences related to sums of divisors
formula: Dirichlet g.f. of row n: zeta(s)*zeta(s-n)/zeta(2*s-n).
